    <a style="font-weight:bold" href="/user/show/4629647-imhear-a-little-haze">Éimhear (A Little Haze)</a>

      
<span id="freeTextContainer1396911276860312458">It isn&apos;t needed. It just isn&apos;t. It is reinforcing negative connotations that are completely unfounded in the first place! So I 100% agree with you tha</span>
  <span id="freeText1396911276860312458" style="display:none">It isn't needed. It just isn't. It is reinforcing negative connotations that are completely unfounded in the first place! So I 100% agree with you that there was absolutely no need to require the introduction of race in that instance. I know I did not read the book but I just cannot see how it was integral to the plot! It just seems to be so ingrained in the collective ideal of normal or expected behaviour that an issue such as this is often overlooked by us as readers. I know that I myself am utterly guilty of this. That's why it is important to constantly challenge ourselves. Forget other people and start with ourselves, and learn to think more critically without it being this great effort. Well that's what I try to do anyway. I know I'm hopelessly flawed and full of my own cultural bias but I'm getting there....slowly!</span>
