  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3234010914" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3234010914" />
    <a title="Adam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1083458-adam"><img alt="Adam" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643050437p2/1083458.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3234010914?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adam" href="/user/show/1083458-adam">Adam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3234010914" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16906100401691512893">Hypnotic terror. All the captivating, brutal elan of a putrid virus of words, spread on page after page, in home after home, where hiding in indefinite quarantine is the surest way to be cornered. For all that ferocity and imminent-cum-ongoing doom, LK displays and defends an elegant rhetoric, the virtuoso wordsmith, spieling nothing but last breaths, with whom we have the dismal privilege of sharing the deck on this Titanic Earth. And boy howdy the sea is rising fast.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

